9. SEARCH & AVAILABILITY
-----------------------

Search Inputs:
- City
- Location
- VehicleType
- Optional filters:
  - brand
  - transmission
  - fuelType

Data Structures (Discussed Options):

Option 1: Simple List
- List<Vehicle>
- Linear scan (O(n))
- Acceptable for small fleets

Option 2: Nested Map (Preferred for optimization)
- Map<Brand, Map<Model, Map<Transmission, Map<FuelType, Set<Vehicle>>>>>
- Lookup time proportional to depth (treated as near-constant)
- Improves search performance

Availability Rules:
- Vehicle must be AVAILABLE
- Vehicle must not be reserved in overlapping time window

-----------------------------------------------------

10. LOCATION MANAGER (CORE LOGIC)
--------------------------------

Class: LocationManager
----------------------
Attributes:
- locationId
- Map<VehicleId, Vehicle>
- Locking mechanism (conceptual)

Methods:
- searchVehicles(filters, timeWindow)
- reserveVehicle(user, vehicleId, startTime, endTime)
- cancelReservation(reservationId)
- pickupVehicle(reservationId)
- returnVehicle(reservationId)

Responsibilities:
- Core orchestration class
- Handles reservation lifecycle
- Ensures no double booking
- Updates vehicle status correctly

-----------------------------------------------------

11. RESERVATION FLOW
-------------------

Reserve Vehicle:
1. User selects city → location → vehicle
2. LocationManager checks availability
3. Lock is acquired (optimistic or pessimistic)
4. Vehicle status updated to RESERVED
5. Reservation object created
6. Payment recorded
7. Reservation confirmed

Pickup Vehicle:
1. Reservation validated
2. Reservation status → CONFIRMED
3. Vehicle status → RENTED

Return Vehicle:
1. Reservation closed
2. Reservation status → COMPLETED
3. Vehicle status → AVAILABLE
4. Vehicle added back to available pool

-----------------------------------------------------

12. CONCURRENCY HANDLING
-----------------------

Discussed Strategies:

Pessimistic Locking:
- Lock vehicle or reservation record
- Strong consistency
- Lower concurrency
- Simple mental model

Optimistic Locking:
- Versioning / retry on conflict
- Higher concurrency
- Requires conflict handling

Interview Position:
- Choose based on business priority
- Strong consistency preferred to avoid double booking

-----------------------------------------------------

13. DESIGN PRINCIPLES FOLLOWED
-----------------------------

- Single Responsibility Principle
- Open/Closed Principle
- Strategy Pattern for Pricing
- Composition over Inheritance
- Separation of concerns
- No God classes

